<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7174523>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. A, Pleurocodonellina microperforata Tilbrook, 2006, with one ovicellate zooid and a small avicularium adjacent to each orifice; B‒D, Arthropoma subarensis, new species, at three magnifications; note the four arrowed spine bases in C, with paired spine bases in ovicellate zooids; D shows the reticulate dimpled patterning of the ovicell endooecium, with minute perforations at the bottom of each dimple. Scale bars = 0.5 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C); 0. 1 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7174523/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

